@node "BUFFYTHEMOVIE" "Buffy.guide: Buffy The Vampire Slayer (Movie)"

@{b}Buffy The Vampire Slayer@{ub}
(The Movie)

Surprisingly few people know about the Buffy movie (released in 1992, four years before the series started) and fewer have watched it so I've decided to write a synopsis for the film. Viewers hoping for one and a half hours of big-screen Sarah Michelle Gellar will be greatly dissappointed (Buffy is played by Kristy Swanson), and of course there's no Willow, Xander or Giles.

Joss Whedon wasn't happy with the way the film eventually turned out because it was so far removed from his original vision. Critics view the film as a major flop and it's screened only when Channel 5 run out of things to play for the 9 o'clock movie slot. So if you can't get hold of it (or would rather imagine Sarah doing Buffy's vamp-dusting deeds) here's the basic outline...

...Uh, sometime soon. *Cough* Y'know, during my hiatus i saw this for sale on DVD. Didn't buy it. Stoopid! Here's a little blurb I found from Blackstar.co.uk in the meantime...

The movie that started it all. Blonde, bouncy Buffy (Kristy Swanson) is your typical high school cheerleader - her goal is to "marry a star and die" and nothing gets in her way when its time to shop. But all that changes when a strange man (Donald Sutherland) informs her she's been chosen by fate to kill vampires. With the help of a romantic rebel (Luke Perry), Buffy is soon spending school nights protecting L.A. from Lothos, the vampire king (Rutger Hauer), his sidekick, Lefty (Paul Reubens), and their determined gang of bloodsuckers. It's everything you'd expect from a teen queen in the valley.

